org.logicmill.util.hash

Class SpookyHash64

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.logicmill.util.hash.SpookyHash64

  • public class SpookyHash64
extends java.lang.Object
    A variation of SpookyHash for use in applications that require only 64-bit hash code values. When compared to SpookyHash, the following differences are noted:
    • The computation is identical to 128-bit SpookyHash; only the method signatures and the use of the seed value are changed.
    • The seed value for SpookyHash64 is a single long value, which is duplicated to populate the internal 128-seed value.
    • The 64-bit long hash code is always returned as the function value.
    Author:
    David Curtis
    See Also:
    SpookyHash

        int start,
        int length,
        long seed)
        Computes the hash code for an array of bytes, using the specified seed value.
        Parameters:
        src - contains bytes for which the hash code is computed
        start - the index of the first element in src to include in the computation; must be non-negative and no larger than src.length
        length - the number of bytes to include in the computation; must be non-negative and no larger than src.length - start
        seed - seed value used to initialize engine state
        Returns:
        computed hash code
        Throws:
        java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException - if the preconditions for offset or length do not obtain
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if length is negative
